\b Getting Started
\b0 \
\
The contents of the Template Pack folder make it easy for you to start writing pages. There are three folders inside: assets, images, and info. Place those three folders together in whatever directory makes sense to you, but I recommend making it easy to navaigate to since you will need the ability "open" the page in a browser. The three folders must remain as you see them in the Template Pack folder; in other words, all in the same directory (but not necessarily insides the Template Pack folder).\
\
The template is in the info folder. Once you start working, create a copy of the template.htm to work from and save it in the info folder. If you accidentally save content into the template. No biggie, just read the Fixme at the bottom. Save the file name something that pertains to the content, but has no spaces like hairCutsForHatWearers.htm or findUs.htm. Try to avoid abbreviations (except in the most obvious of cases) and use camelCase: other than the first word, everyword in the name of the file starts with a capital letter like hairCutsForHatWearers. All of that is a suggestion, except no spaces. You can't have spaces in URLs. While many browsers today can handle it if we use HTML special character substitutions, writing those in is a pain and prone to time-wasting errors. Oh and for the same reason no special chracters like accented or most punctuation. Allowed characters are . (period) and _ (underscore). Once the page is saved using a new name, you can move on to editing.\
\

\b Editors
\b0 \
Open the page in your favorite editor. It is just as easy when working with basic HTML to work with a simple text editor like NotePad (Windows) or TextEdit (Mac; but it must be configured for plain text instead of the default RTF). But you can use more sophisticated apps that help highlight syntax errors. Komodo Edit (no longer my favorite), BBEdit (tho that might be Mac only .... not sure and you need to add plugins to understand HTML). Sublime text, or Visual Studio Code (if I have that installed, it is probably free, but it may require a license from your Valencia account to download).\
\

